 lndashen@sfsu.edu wrote:
 
 > I have downloaded mrspidey.exe and mrspidey.ps and put them in
 > c:\program files\plt\ When click mrspidey.exe anything happens.
 > When click mrspidey.ps, it requires winword.exe.  But, after I
 > specify the winword.exe path to request, I just get a unreadable
 > Word file opened.
 
 That's because you need the Ghostview program to view the file.  You
 need to download Ghostview; you can find it at
 
   http://www.cs.wisc.edu/~ghost/
 
 You need to double-click on the .exe, not on the .ps, to install
 MrSpidey.  (I believe that is what our documentation says.)
 
 'shriram

