 Quoting lndashen@sfsu.edu:
 > I have downloaded mrspidey.exe and mrspidey.ps and put them in
 > c:\program files\plt\ When click mrspidey.exe anything happens. When
 > click mrspidey.ps, it requires winword.exe. But, after I specify the
 > winword.exe path to request, I just get a unreadable Word file opened.
 
 Where did you get "mrspidey.exe"? The MrSpidey download page provides
 "mrspidey.plt", not "mrspidey.exe". "Mrspidey.plt" is a file that
 should be dragged onto "Setup PLT" in the plt folder. Then, when you
 start DrScheme, it will contain a "MrSpidey" button.
 
 Unfortunately, I don't know how to print PostScript (.ps) files under
 Windows. Is winword.exe supposed to handle PostScript? If all else
 fails, consider downloading the documentation in HTML format.
 
 Thanks,
 Matthew
 
 
